column5: Just had a wind advisory issued on the 6pm news, 70-90 km/h winds from Grey Bruce through Simcoe County.  Blowing pretty good here already.
Should be a nice walleye chop
Tell ya what,  take a quart of whipping cream along and maybe it will be a real butter churner.
The sound of the waves crashing could be heard miles up the river this morning. It was soooo loud. Lots of downed trees.
